6 discussing the results of the boxplots¶

Boxplots are a method of data presentation that only shows the distribution of the data along with its median and quartiles. Additionally, the outliners have an effect on the boxplot. In this particular scenario, the fruit category has the least amount of sales, making it the shortest one. The longest ones are the ones for cosmetics and household goods. It indicates that the most of our revenue came from sales of cosmetics and household goods. As a result, we need to direct more of our focus toward the category of fruits, which is one in which we can continue to develop more in order to generate more revenue. Additionally, we are able to keep up with our work on cosmetics and household items.

# Write this out to a CSV file called Countries_By_Region.csv.

from itertools import zip_longest
Loc = ListRegions.values()
with open('Data/Countries_By_Region.csv','w+', newline='') as csvfile:
    writer = csv.writer(csvfile)
    writer.writerow(ListRegions.keys())
    for values in zip_longest(*Loc):
        writer.writerow(values)
